H0.text: Which Australian cricketer in his very last innings in 1948 scored a duck (0). Don Bradman

H1.text: Which Australian cricketer in his very last innings in 1948 scored a duck (0). Lindsay Hassett

H2.text: Which Australian cricketer in his very last innings in 1948 scored a duck (0). Arthur Morris

H3.text: Which Australian cricketer in his very last innings in 1948 scored a duck (0). 99.94

A4.text: Facing the wrist-spin of Eric Hollies, Bradman pushed forward to the second ball that he faced, was deceived by a googly, and was bowled between bat and pad for a duck.

A5.text: His career average finished at 99.94; if he had scored just four runs in his last innings, it would have been 100.
